<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-09-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-09-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="489" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">717.2114/71: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Piles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-16T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            16, 1928—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September 17
                                        (<hi rend="smallcaps">?</hi>)—10:20
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>94. Department’s 55, September 15, 1 p.m. Text of treaty has not yet
                                been made public but the President has publicly stated the general
                                provisions of the treaty in his recent annual message to Congress.
                                To date there has been no press comment.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Piles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>